fullTextAnnotation.text:
Class Activity - 4
Write a generator function that takes an array of function as the first argument and
executes them asynchronously, each after a specified delay (second argument).
The generator function should return a set of promises, one after the other, for
each function in the list with the appropriate delays. It should also pass to each
function a parameter representing the current index of the function in the list.
Iterate over the list using the generator and attach a .then and .catch clause to
each of the promises yielded by the generator.
Solution: asyncGenerator.js
